.TH "ipr_initiate_ioa_bringdown" 9 "ipr_initiate_ioa_bringdown" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_initiate_ioa_bringdown \- Bring down an adapter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ipr_initiate_ioa_bringdown
.BI "(struct ipr_ioa_cfg *ioa_cfg "  ","
.BI "enum ipr_shutdown_type shutdown_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioa_cfg" 12
ioa config struct
.IP "shutdown_type" 12
shutdown type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will initiate bringing down the adapter.
This consists of issuing an IOA shutdown to the adapter
to flush the cache, and running BIST.
If the caller needs to wait on the completion of the reset,
the caller must sleep on the reset_wait_q.

Return value:
none
